### Data Flow Stages

**Stage 1: Discovery & Collection**
- Scanner connects via SSH/SNMP
- Collects device metadata and running configs
- Runs on customer premises

**Stage 2: Sanitization (CRITICAL)**
- Config passes through 3-tier sanitizer
- Tier 1: TextFSM templates (precise)
- Tier 2: Section-aware regex (heuristic)
- Tier 3: Aggressive regex (catch-all)
- Redaction log tracks what was removed

**Stage 3: Vectorization**
- Sanitized config converted to embeddings
- 768-dimensional vectors for semantic search

**Stage 4: Cloud Upload**
- Only sanitized data leaves customer network
- Embeddings stored in PostgreSQL (pgvector)
- Topology relationships in Neo4j